Added to the feathers of success being garnered by the Nigerian Military, troops of Air Component of Operation Hadarin Daji have exterminated two terrorists’ commanders identified as in Zamfara State. The duo of Kachalla Ruga and Alhaji Auta was reportedly targeted by the Nigerian Air Force (NAF) aircraft which reports say had bombed terrorists’ hideouts at Gusami Forest and Tsamre Village in Birnin Magaji local government area of the state in the wee hours of Friday. A military source told journalists on Saturday scores of bandits who converged at Auta’s residence for his burial were also killed during the bombardment of the location. #EndSARS Report: Military Breaks Silence, Says Only White Paper… Military Neutralize Four Identified Bandits, Several Others He said: “The whereabouts of other notorious bandits like Alhaji Nashama, Shingi and Halilu remain unknown.”